    "When a question is given, typical generative IR systems (i.e., AI-powered chatbots) extend prompts with likely completions and extract answers from the extended prompts (Najork, 2023).",
    "ChatGPT and Google Gemini are recently developed generative IR applications that have spurred unprecedented universal attention.",
    "Nevertheless, ongoing research is highlighting their drawbacks, such as generating incorrect or unrealistic answers, which is known as the hallucination phenomenon ChatGPT: https://chat.openai.com/.",
    "Google Gemini: https://gemini.google.com/.",
    "Metzler et al. (2021) reported several challenges in generative IRs, such as suggesting contexts for generated answers and considering the authority or quality of documents for answer generation."
